    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Removal and installation of brake switch"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not connect the coupler with the brake switch removed. The engine will recognize that the brake is depressed, and the engine will start with a single press of the ENGINE START STOP button, which is dangerous due to engine starting when not intended."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Brake switch removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "985_3.0_jpn_11337359_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Rotate the brake switch (B) counterclockwise to remove it. Remove the clip (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Brake pedal adjustment",
